│  Title: Deploy Docker Apps to Kubernetes with Jenkins URL Source:                                                                     │
│  https://www.red-gate.com/simple-talk/devops/containers-and-virtualization/deploying-a-dockerized-application-to-the-kubernetes-clus  │
│  ter-using-jenkins/ Published Time: 2023-12-01T14:51:19+00:00 Markdown Content: To deploy a Dockerized application to Kubernetes      │
│  using Jenkins, you create a Jenkins CI/CD pipeline that builds a Docker image, pushes it to Docker Hub, and then uses kubectl to     │
│  deploy it to a Kubernetes cluster. This tutorial walks through the complete workflow using a Jenkinsfile with stages for building,   │
│  pushing, pulling, and deploying a containerized application to a Minikube cluster. You will install the Docker Pipeline and          │
│  Kubernetes plugins in Jenkins, configure credentials, and write a multi-stage pipeline that automates the entire deployment          │
│  process. ## Introduction [Jenkins](https://www.jenkins.io/) serves as an open-source automation server with widespread application   │
│  in the realm of software development, primarily focusing on continuous integration (CI) and continuous delivery (CD). Its core       │
│  purpose revolves around streamlining the management and automation of diverse tasks associated with software project development,    │
│  including building, testing, and deployment. Jenkins effectively empowers development teams to mechanize the process of              │
│  incorporating code changes from numerous contributors, executing automated tests, and deploying applications to diverse              │
│  environments. It ensures the soft                                                                                                    │
