│  cluster](https://docs.gitlab.com/user/clusters/agent/install/). When done, you have a Kubernetes context and can run Kubernetes API  │
│  commands in your GitLab CI/CD pipeline. To ensure access to your cluster is safe: * Each agent has a separate context                │
│  (`kubecontext`). * Only the project where the agent is configured, and any additional projects you authorize, can access the agent   │
│  in your cluster. To use GitLab CI/CD to interact with your cluster, runners must be registered with GitLab. However, these runners   │
│  do not have to be in the cluster where the agent is. Prerequisites: * Make sure [GitLab CI/CD is                                     │
