│  causes real problems. I’ve seen deployments fail because images were too large for the available bandwidth. I’ve debugged            │
│  applications that worked locally but failed in production because of subtle differences in base images. I’ve watched teams struggle  │
│  with inconsistent builds because they didn’t understand image caching. The key insight I’ve learned: treat images as a product, not  │
│  just a build artifact. They need versioning, testing, and optimization just like your application code. ## Understanding Image       │
